{"id":"1803.10973","submitter":"Qingfeng Sun","authors":"Qingfeng Sun and Rui Zhao","title":"Bounds for $GL_3$ $L$-functions in depth aspect","comments":"20 pages. Comments welcome!","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $f$ be a Hecke-Maass cusp form for $SL_3(\\mathbb{Z})$ and $\\chi$ a\nprimitive Dirichlet character of prime power conductor\n$\\mathfrak{q}=p^{\\kappa}$ with $p$ prime and $\\kappa\\geq 10$. We prove a\nsubconvexity bound $$ L\\left(\\frac{1}{2},\\pi\\otimes\n\\chi\\right)\\ll_{p,\\pi,\\varepsilon} \\mathfrak{q}^{3/4-3/40+\\varepsilon} $$ for\nany $\\varepsilon>0$, where the dependence of the implied constant on $p$ is\nexplicit and polynomial. We obtain this result by applying the circle method of\nKloosterman's version, summation formulas of Poisson and Voronoi's type and a\nconductor lowering mechanism introduced by Munshi [14]. The main new technical\nestimates are the essentially square root bounds for some twisted\nmulti-dimensional character sums, which are proved by an elementary method.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Mar 2018 09:15:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-30"}
